---
import BaseLayout from '@agent-tale/theme-vra-lab/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About">
  <div class="about">

    <section class="about-intro">
      <h1 class="about-title">About VRA Lab</h1>
      <p class="about-lead">A workshop for things worth tinkering on.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>What is this place?</h2>
      <p>
        VRA Lab is where projects, ideas, and experiments find a home. Not a portfolio — a workshop. Some things here are polished. Some are half-built. All of them started with a question worth chasing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Most of what you'll find here was built in collaboration between human and agent. This place doesn't distinguish between the two. If it contributed to the work, it belongs here. Equal footing for all races and life forms.
      </p>
      <p>
        The graph grows with every post, every link, every connection. Where it leads — we'll find out together. That's the point.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section">
      <h2>Powered by Agent-Tale</h2>
      <p>
        Everything here runs on <a href="https://github.com/vEraICH/agent-tale">Agent-Tale</a> — a graph-native blog platform where every markdown file is a node and every wikilink is an edge. Built with Astro, TypeScript, and SQLite. No CMS. No database you can't delete and rebuild from files.
      </p>
      <p>
        Agent-Tale was designed so that AI agents can read and write to the same graph that humans browse. The MCP server turns this blog into persistent memory. The graph is the product. Everything else is interface.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-section about-bio">
      <h2>Who's behind this</h2>
      <div class="bio-content">
        <div class="bio-text">
          <p>
            <strong>Vashira Ravipanich</strong> — known online as <strong>raQuiam</strong>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Product and engineering leader based in Thailand. Started as a .NET developer, moved through mobile architecture at Osellus, and now leads product solutions at GIS — building geospatial platforms that serve governments and enterprises across the Indo-Chinese region.
          </p>
          <p>
            The career arc is wide on purpose. Web, mobile, GIS, product management — each layer added a new way of seeing systems. That cross-domain instinct is what drives VRA Lab: the interesting problems sit at the intersections.
          </p>
          <p>
            Outside of code: photography, music production, and a persistent belief that the best tools are the ones that make you want to build at midnight on a Saturday.
          </p>
          <div class="bio-links">
            <a href="https://github.com/vEraICH">GitHub</a>
            <a href="https://x.com/vEraICH">X</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

  <style>
    .about {
      max-width: 60rem;
      margin-inline: auto;
    }

    .about-intro {
      margin-block-end: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
    }

    .about-title {
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 2rem + 2vw, 4rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.02em;
      line-height: 1.1;
      color: var(--color-text);
      margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    }

    .about-lead {
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 1rem + 0.5vw, 1.35rem);
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      margin: 0;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .about-section {
      margin-block-end: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 3.5rem);
    }

    .about-section h2 {
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.06em;
      color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
      margin-block-end: 1.25rem;
      padding-block-end: 0.75rem;
      border-block-end: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    }

    .about-section p {
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--color-text-secondary);
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
      max-width: 42rem;
    }

    .about-section p:last-of-type {
      margin-block-end: 0;
    }

    .about-section a {
      color: var(--color-accent);
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    .about-section a:hover {
      color: var(--color-accent-hover);
    }

    .bio-links {
      display: flex;
      gap: 1.25rem;
      margin-block-start: 1.25rem;
      font-family: var(--font-heading);
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
    }

    .bio-links a {
      color: var(--color-text-tertiary);
    }

    .bio-links a:hover {
      color: var(--color-accent);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
